---
import BaseLayout from "../layouts/BaseLayout.astro";
---

<BaseLayout
  title="About | SecurityNotionsZoo"
  description="About SecurityNotionsZoo, a taxonomy of cryptographic security notions for Fully Homomorphic Encryption."
>
  <div class="mb-10">
    <a href="/" class="text-sky-600 dark:text-accent hover:text-sky-500 dark:hover:text-sky-300 text-sm font-medium inline-flex items-center gap-1 mb-8 decoration-transparent transition-colors">
      <svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" width="16" height="16" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round"><path d="m15 18-6-6 6-6"/></svg>
      Back to taxonomy
    </a>

    <h1 class="text-4xl md:text-5xl font-extrabold text-slate-900 dark:text-slate-100 mb-3 tracking-tight transition-colors">
      About
    </h1>
    <p class="text-xl md:text-2xl text-slate-600 dark:text-slate-400 font-medium max-w-3xl leading-snug transition-colors">
      Why this site exists and who built it
    </p>
  </div>

  <div class="prose prose-slate dark:prose-invert prose-a:text-sky-600 dark:prose-a:text-accent hover:prose-a:text-sky-500 dark:hover:prose-a:text-sky-300 max-w-none prose-headings:text-slate-900 dark:prose-headings:text-slate-200 transition-colors text-justify">

    <h2>Motivation</h2>
    <p>
      Fully Homomorphic Encryption (FHE) is a rapidly evolving field, and the number of security notions used to analyze FHE schemes has grown with it.
      Keeping track of what exists, what each notion captures, and how they relate to one another and how to achieve them has become genuinely difficult.
    </p>
    <p>
      SecurityNotionsZoo aims to be a structured, accessible reference that maps this space: a living taxonomy where notions are defined, linked to their source papers, and placed in relation to each other.
    </p>

    <h2>Aim</h2>
    <p>
      The goal of this site is to help researchers and practitioners navigate the security notions relevant to FHE, whether they are choosing a notion for a new construction, understanding a proof in a paper, or simply trying to get oriented in the field.
      The relation graph on the home page gives a bird's-eye view of the implication structure, while individual notion pages provide definitions, references, and context.
    </p>

    <h2>Contributors</h2>
    <p>
      This website was created by <a href="https://www.jdumezy.com" target="_blank">Jules Dumezy</a>, who also maintains it.
      We thank our contributors, who helped grow the site by adding notions and improving the content:
    </p>
    <ul>
      <li>Marc Renard</li>
    </ul>

    <h2>Errors and contributions</h2>
    <p>
      Despite our best efforts, this site may contain errors in definitions, relations, or references.
      If you spot a mistake or would like to add a notion, please
      <a href="https://github.com/jdumezy/securitynotionszoo/issues" target="_blank">open an issue</a> or
      <a href="https://github.com/jdumezy/securitynotionszoo/pulls" target="_blank">submit a pull request</a> on GitHub.
      You can also reach out directly to <a href="https://www.jdumezy.com" target="_blank">Jules Dumezy</a>.
      Contributions are very welcome.
    </p>

  </div>
</BaseLayout>
